<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hold the Z for -IZE:</span> If you have I and E tiles alongside Z, you have the suffix ready. Look for 4-5 letter roots on the board or in your rack. REAL+IZE, ORGAN+IZE, FINAL+IZE — the combinations are endless.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Premium square targeting:</span> Z on a double or triple letter score turns a good play into a devastating one. A Z on DLS adds 20 points; on TLS it adds 30. Position -IZE words to land Z on premium squares whenever possible.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Bingo factory potential:</span> -IZE creates natural 7-8 letter bingos. Keep the suffix tiles together and build from common stems: STERIL+IZE, PATRON+IZE, CAPITAL+IZE. The 50-point bonus plus Z value makes these plays game-winners.</p>
  </div>
</div>

